caption: Awesome and fresh food, I loved the vibes the place has, and the cashiers were very welcoming. Will definitely come back again.

Their best is fried wings! Others are so-so. Make sure you have tried their wings, no matter which flavor !

Bad experience with this restaurant. Ordered a soup with pork morsels in it, and got a plastic container with a watery soup that had shards of bone throughout. And the few pork "morsels" were mostly bone and gristle.  I ordered what I saw on a menu photo and what I got was nothing like it.  Not the pork cubes shown. Not the consistency shown.  The bone pieces made it impossible to eat the meal. And there was not even a plastic ot coated paper bowl. Tiny plastic spoon. When I asked why what I got was different from the meal pictured, I was told the photo was just for show.  Pure misrepresentation and bad customer service. Stay away..

We had a great experience at this spot. We liked the wonderful atmosphere and the meals. The waiters are super affable. I’m content we ultimately managed to try this place.

Zaab wings are a ripoff. Sometimes you get whole wings, sometimes you get half of what you got the first time. No consistency in portions and the chicken is super rubbery and chewy. It’s like eating a salty rubber band.
Zabb wings was really spicy, taste is a really good and quick. Prices are fair enough.

The Zaab Wings were amazing here, they are extremely spicy and kind of on the salty side.  I personally don't love spicy foods but the flavor was soooooooo good I dealt with the spiciness.  If you like dry ribs the Zaab Wings are definitely for you!
Food just ok much better food stalls to choose from

Tried the grilled mushroom salad, green papaya salad and the zaab wings; all awesome. The flavors here are centered on fish sauce, fresh garlic, lime and hot hot hot peppers (although they can adjust the spice level to your taste). This place is a fine new addition to the food hall and it seems like they are responding to feedback and have made improvements/adjustments to their operations since opening.

Not going back! This is my second time ordering from this place. I got the Laab Mu the first time and it was great and the portion was good. I was shopping at Trader Joe’s and decided to ordered the Laab a second time, to go. When I got home,  the portion was literally a quarter of what I got the first time, which was laughable. It was 3/4 vegetables and 1/4 mince pork. Very disappointing because I felt ripped off paying $13.00 for mince pork that was the size of half my palm and majority of vegetables. The Laab is good but just check the portion if you  are ordering it to go.
The spicy pork riblet soup is spicy indeed, and delicious!
Outrageously salty. Decent flavors, but practically inedible due to the salt
one of the best chicken dishes I've ever had!
Pork shoulder was outrageously delicious

Located in Dekalb Market hall. The service was friendly at the ordering station. Food came out quickly after ordering. The menu is pretty limited and easy. Variety of Thai dishes. You have the chicken, half or whole that comes with rice and spicy dipping sauce. The papaya salad packed a punch in flavors and spice at medium level. The grilled pork shoulder and laab mu (pork) and seems pretty popular is the Zaab wings. We shared the chicken, laab mu and papaya salad.  I really liked the chicken. Is was juicy and flavorful. The accompanying dipping sauce added a nice spiciness to it. The papaya salad was full of flavor and plenty of umami with bits of tiny dried shrimp and fish sauce. The cabbage and cucumber added a nice level of crunch. The laab mu went great with rice. This one is a bit more watery (sauce) than others I've tried (which was dryer and slightly crispy - which I think I liked better).  I will definitely be ordering more from them. I like that it seems like more healthy option if you keep from the fried wings. Spice level is moderate on the medium level. It isn't overly spicy but enough to know it is there. I tend to like it slightly hotter but you can adjust as you like when ordering.

The zaab wings are fire! If you like serious heat in your food, this is the place and the dish for you. The wings have a distinct chili-lime flavoring. It's a unique flavor combination and both flavors are prominently on display. I'm wasn't a fan of their sticky rice, but their jasmine rice is just plain ol' jasmine rice. Pro tip: Take the coating from the zaab wings and sprinkle it onto the sticky rice, or just dump the rice into the box with the wings so that it can soak up the coating. Trust me, it'll be good.  When CI first opened they'd serve the wing pieces intact. Now, they separate the drums and flats, which is a decision that I wasn't happy about, but the wings still have the same great taste. Honestly, I'm wondering if they've turned up the heat and made them even hotter.
Had quite a bit of heat and very authentic flavors! Got the Laab Mu and fully enjoyed it!
Chicken wings were succulent and juicy but the seasoning they put on was way toooooo salty. Good heat but they need to take care with the salt.  Potential here.

If you like the real deal and authentic Thai food, then Chicks Isan is the only place. The taste is sOo flavorful and soOo mouthwatering especially the Isan style grilled chicken, grilled pork cheeks, larb moo, papaya salad, and the crispy rice salad! Hands down the best new addition to Dekalb Market Hall.

Visited Chicks Isan on Wednesday and easy to see that they just opened by how disorganized they were and that everything was served in these containers. Apparently they have a seafood restaurant in the city as well.  The first dish is called Larb Moo which is minced pork tossed with Thai herbs. According to the menu online and at the location for $9 it’s suppose to come with toasted sticky rice but the person swore that rice is an extra $3 bucks so I got jasmine instead. I did not know nor did the counter person mention anything about heat and boy was my mouth on fire 🔥. If we put my destroyed 🤦🏻‍♂️ taste buds aside the food actually had pretty good flavors. I ended up eating only 1/4 of the dish and took the rest home to let my wife taste the fire.  The second picture is of a fried chicken wing I stole from a coworker they call “Zaab Wings”. Here you get a slight bit of heat on the back end with strong lime flavors. I wish I bought this instead as i was able to actually eat this and enjoy with what was left of my taste buds.  Overall the verdict is that it will be a good addition once the bumps are worked out and they get a control on there heat levels.
